' @id(DOM-CANVAS-VIEW)
' @desc(DOM-CANVAS-VIEW, "Code struct CanvasView: base zoom and pan plus the center-fixed fisheye parameters (enabled, strength, radius); focal() returns the canvas-rect centre.")
' Current-side domain derived from `struct CanvasView` in
' crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs.
title Diagram canvas view state (current)

class CanvasView <<added>> {
  + base_zoom : f32
  + pan : Vec2
  + fisheye_enabled : bool
  + fisheye_strength : f32
  + fisheye_radius : f32
  + focal(rect) : Pos2
  + warp(p, focal) : Pos2
  + fisheye_mesh(tex, rect, focal) : Mesh
}

note bottom of CanvasView
  base_zoom is changed only by scroll-at-cursor; pan
  only by drag. focal(rect) = rect.center() (center-fixed,
  OCL-FISHEYE-FOCAL-CENTER). fisheye_radius is recomputed
  each frame as the farthest-corner distance (> 0).
  fisheye_strength is clamped to [0,1]; 0 short-circuits
  warp() to the plain base placement.
end note
@enduml
